statements: SELECT * FROM health_data;
SELECT user_id, date, steps FROM health_data ORDER BY date DESC;
SELECT user_id, calories_burned FROM health_data WHERE steps > 10000;
SELECT AVG(steps) as average_steps FROM health_data;
SELECT user_id, SUM(calories_burned) as total_calories_burned FROM health_data GROUP BY user_id HAVING total_calories_burned > 500;
SELECT user_id, date, steps, calories_burned, sleep_hours FROM health_data WHERE user_id = 1 AND date = '2022-01-01';
SELECT * FROM health_data WHERE calories_burned > 500 AND sleep_hours < 7 ORDER BY date DESC, steps ASC;
SELECT user_id, date, steps FROM health_data WHERE steps < 5000 OR calories_burned > 700 GROUP BY date ORDER BY date ASC;
SELECT AVG(steps) AS avg_steps, MAX(calories_burned) AS max_calories FROM health_data GROUP BY user_id HAVING avg_steps > 10000;
SELECT user_id, SUM(steps) AS total_steps FROM health_data GROUP BY user_id HAVING total_steps > 50000 ORDER BY total_steps DESC, user_id ASC;
